<h1>My Phone Numbers</h1>

<p>
<%= link_to 'Add phone number', new_user_phone_number_path(current_user) %>
(including country code)
</p>

This can be your mobile, desk phones, or SIP number.  Check forward if you want to forward incoming calls to the number.
Only specify one number to be default.  Default number is used when you place calls.  It is the device that OpenVoice
calls first before connecting your caller.

<table>
  <tr class="header">
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Number</th>
    <th>Forward</th>
    <th>Default</th>
    <th />
    <th />
  </tr>

  <% @phone_numbers.each do |phone_number| %>
  <tr id="phone_number_<%= phone_number.id %>">
    <td><%= on_the_spot_edit phone_number, :name %></td>
    <td><%= on_the_spot_edit phone_number, :number %></td>
    <td><%= on_the_spot_edit phone_number, :forward %></td>
    <td><%= on_the_spot_edit phone_number, :default %></td>
    <td class="narrow"><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_user_phone_number_path(current_user, phone_number) %></td>
    <td class="narrow"><%= link_to 'Delete', "/users/" + current_user.id.to_s + "/phone_numbers/" + phone_number.id.to_s + ".js", "data-remote" => true, :method => :delete %></td>
  </tr>
  <% end %>
</table>